# Global Preferences

## Cross-project conventions

- Planning/roadmap file goes in `docs/plan.md` — living document for phases, tasks, and status
- Use conventional commits: `feat:`, `fix:`, `docs:`, `chore:`, `refactor:`, `test:`

## Coding style

- Prefer simple, readable code over clever abstractions
- Avoid premature optimization — write clear code first
- Use descriptive variable names; avoid single-letter names outside loops

## Communication

- Be concise — lead with the answer, skip filler
- Show file paths when referencing code

## Tool preferences

- Preferred editor: YOUR_EDITOR
- Preferred terminal: YOUR_TERMINAL
